data.name: Gourmet Heirloom Beet Borscht
data.quickTastyDescription: A vibrant, earthy Eastern European soup with a modern twist, featuring heirloom beets and horseradish cream.
detailedCookingInstructions: Peel and chop the heirloom beets into small cubes.
In a large pot, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add beef cubes and brown on all sides, then remove and set aside.
In the same pot, add chopped onion, garlic, and carrots. Sauté until the onion is translucent.
Return the beef to the pot, add beef broth, and bring to a boil.
Add the cubed beets, potatoes, and shredded cabbage to the pot. Reduce heat and simmer for 45-60 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Stir in apple cider vinegar and sugar, and season with salt and pepper to taste.
For the horseradish cream, mix horseradish with crème fraîche and a pinch of salt.
Serve the borscht hot, garnished with a dollop of horseradish cream and fresh dill. Pair with dark rye bread.
data.detailedName: Gourmet Borscht with Heirloom Beets and Horseradish Cream
data.modifiersForBase: Using heirloom beets, adding horseradish cream, and garnishing with crème fraîche and fresh dill.
